So basically a whole term has gone by between my last post and this one and let me tell you.... well not much has happened. Let me sum it up for you:

-Lucy came to visit. Very fun!! So good to see her.
-I went to class. A lot.
-I did homework. A lot.
-I planned many things that did not end up happening. Camping people!!!
-I got super drunk at Cafe Crepe of all places and fell down twice. Well I was pushed over the first time. But hey, at least I didn't end up in a puddle like one friend. (Have been drinking more than this- don't worry! This night just stands out to me)
-Experienced the apocalypse: Vancouver with more than 3 inches of snow. It's been weeks and a main road is STILL closed!
-Dealt with non-drinkable tap water for weeks. Stupid turbidity.
-I did a bit more homework.
-Went to more classes.

And that's about it. But despite the lack of huge events it's been a really good term. Now if only the stupid exams would just be over!!

Well I started packing today for going back to Vancouver on Monday. My room is an absolute tip right now. Have basically filled the bigger of the 2 bags I can bring and that's just with my clothes- haven't even started with the random stuff all over my room. Plus there's still some clothes that are being washed or need to be washed. Oh and my wellies! Must not forget them even though the one time I wore them they absolutely killed my feet. They're just so cute!

I just cannot believe that summer is over. My last shift at work was yesterday, so strange. No more having to work in a shop with broken air conditioning. It's sad though, I'll miss it. Not the evil customers though. God people are so rude!

Well I'm off to get ready for going out for dinner.

Omg summer's almost over... at least that means work is almost over too! I like it but it's making me feel ill. We have no air conditioning and whenever I'm there I get a headache and start feeling dizzy. It's not very enjoyable. I'm sooo tired and have so much to do! Like clean my room. blah!

This is mainly for my benefit as my goal this summer is to read as when I have to go to classes and stuff I never seem to have time to read. Hoping this list will keep me inspired to read. Already Read: Wicked- Gregory Maguire Deafening- Frances Itani Best of Friends- Cathy Kelly Small Island- Andrea Levy The Kite Runner- Khaled Hosseini The Lovely Bones - Alice Sebold The Time Traveler's Wife- Audrey Niffenegger What to Read Next: The Birth House- Ami McKay The Glass Castle- Jeannette Walls The Time Traveler's Wife- Audrey Niffenegger Stuart: A Life Backwards- Alexander Masters Anyone have any book suggestions?? Last updated: July 4, 06

One of the kids I babysit, Helen, has offered me a voucher thing she got at christmas for a guest to have a free horse ride. I think she really wants me to do it but in between me moving here and so stopping my horse riding lessons and now I have developed a little phobia of horses. Not really sure how it happened though- I used to love them! I haven't been riding in years! I told her I'd think about it- could be fun... but what is I squish the horsie?!

I finally have a job! :D Working in a clothing store called New Look- not where I shop for my clothes but it has some nice stuff but more importantly I will be getting paid! Yay! Start tomorrow doing a 4 hour shift, wow haven't had a 4 hour shift in almost a year (haven't had a shift at all but that's besides the point). I hope it all goes well! I'm not the most stylish person ever but apparently I'm good enough. In the interview I had to put together an outfit that was suitable for a picnic during the day but could be changed easily to a dance at night- thought I hadn't done too well but it doesn't matter now. Yay!

Oooh gotta go babysit.

I'm getting sick :( It is not fun, not at all. And I have no idea where people are today. Totally don't feel like going into town and to a bunch of clubs tonight which I'm thinking is the plan for most people. Blah. oh well.

Got my hair cut yesterday but the hair dresser curled it instead of straightening it so don't really know what the cut actually looks like, prob what it looked like before hehe. The colour's nice though, nice and blonde :)

I saw Miss Saigon last night with Charlotte and Danielle, was really good! Sad though. Didn't really know what it was about going but it was a good story, but wehy did it have to end sadly?? Was joking with Danielle that if I for some reason ever made a musical I'd just change the sad ending of one that already existed and make it happy. Everyone loves a happy ending!

Not too much else happening, taking Danielle to the bus station in a bit since she's going back to Glasgow. I think I'm going out into town tonight with Charlotte and Val, not sure if anyone else is going but should hopefully be fun :)

Well since Lucy keeps bugging me to update (even though she hasn't for over a year!!) I decided today would be the day. And since I've doen absolutely nothing the past couple weeks this is going to be a super boring update.

So have been home from uni for just less than 2 weeks and have done basically nothing, I have attempted to find a job (absolutely no jobs available right now!!), seen a couple friends, but everyone is either not in Aberdeen or working all week if they are here. Thankfully Danielle will be back for a week from Thurs before abandoning me again! But Charc will be back the 20th for good. So the past couple days I have done absolutely nothing, I've watched tv and walked my dog. I've barely even driven, should really drive today although no idea where. May pick up Danielle from bus station on Thurs which she'll be happy about.

So yeah, nothing's happening at all. I just made myself lunch. Very exciting. Umm... listening to Van Halen right now... yeah that's about it.

Writing this anthro essay (due tomorrow) is driving me insane. I started incorporating parts of disney movies and Lost into it which is strange. Anyway taking a short break to give my laptop time to charge a little (brain too).

Ew, my banana has a big bruise :( Sad now.
I freakin' love musicals!! I totally just remembered how much and why. They make me so happy! Eeeee! I want to go to London and NYC! I want to see more!

First final tomorrow and what do I do today?? Not a lot! I should just go to bed right now, but I just feel like reading. Stupid physics, I hope it goes ok.

1 month and 1 day and then it's Christmas!!

I think I should officially be allowed to celebrate.
I want to sleep. I don't want to learn physics. Sleeeeeeeeeeeeep!
I hate math, la la la.

I wanna be Cruella DeVil for Halloween. That'd be so cool! Hehe a group of us are going to Playland the Friday before Halloween and are getting dressed up and stuff. Should be good, lots of rides and like 5 'Haunted Houses'. Scary. hehe.

I'm strange today. I finish class an hour and a half earlier than usual so get back to my room around 10:30 and just hop into bed, next thing I know it's 20 to 1 and I was meant to meet people for lunch at 12, so I go and grab some food to bring back then sit infront of tv watching nothing really then go back to my room and watch a dvd which I half sleep through. And even now all I feel like doing is sleeping. Why am I so tired today? It's not as though I got no sleep last night... although I did have a weird dream so maybe that messed with my deep sleepingness.

So bored. Lalala, meant to be studying. Stupid physics midterm. I wish there was a holiday coming up. Like a long holiday. I want summer all year long! 

I put up a bunch of pics today so I'm feeling better about my room, has more stuff to make it feel more like home. I wish I had more pics from this past month though. I haven't been taking any pics and I know it's gonna annoy me later. I like having pics to remember randomn things.

Still haven't cleaned my room, that was my goal for this weekend but I somehow found other things to do. Doesn't even feel like it was a long weekend sadly. Anyway I'd better get going and attempt to look at some physics... or wash my hair. It's kinda gross right now.
Omg... I'm actually going off campus tonight. I'm going to eat non-cafeteria food! And go to the cinema. I feel normal again, not some strange person trapped on campus. Totally excited. Hehe.

Once upon a time there lived a giant piece of corn. His name was Fred. One evening Fred went to the grocery cart because he felt hungry. So then he bought seventeen litres of milk and eighty-two bottles of purple juice. After that he met Sally and they saw a movie at the grocery cart parking lot. When they sat to watch the movie Sally fell to her death. Fred was shocked and very sad so he decided to go to the circus and become a lion tamer. After he decided to become a monkey's friend, the lions just weren't cutting it. They were very upset that he abandoned them, but they smelled funny so it all worked out ok. 

One day Fred's best friend decided that they were going to go on a vacation away from the circus together. Fred agreed and they set out to decide where to go. they figured that they would travel approximately 43 degrees north west until they came upon a hamburger stand where they decided to stop to get a bite eat. It was there that they met Collette. She was so ugly that they did not know what to say, but she did not know what to say either. For what do you say to a giant piece of corn and his best friend?

To be continued....

See you next time, same bat time , same bat channel.

By Sarah and Christy

My shoes hurt me.

I am in Canada. So sunny and hot! Feeling kinda strange to be spending everyday with my mom though. Usually I have my friends to do things with but I have no friends here. Great fun. Move into res in about a week and a half so I shall meet people then and hopefully have friends again. Plans for tomorrow are to go buy a computer, look at the house my parents own and go out to dinner with my Grandma and Aunt and Uncle which should be nice. No idea how well we'll stick to the plan though. May also try and find some new ceramic hair straighteners. Anyway I'd better go. I just wanna get back to my Aunty's house and read my book...it's getting interesting and that's a ways away from my sisters apartment (where I am now).

http://news.yahoo.com/news?tmpl=story&u=/playbill/20050812/en_playbill/94526

Guettel and Goldman to Team on 'Princess Bride' Musical 
Robert Simonson Playbill On-Line 
Fri Aug 12, 2:45 PM ET


Composer Adam Guettel and screenwriter William Goldman will collaborate on a musical version or the hit fairy tale film "The Princess Bride," the New York Post reported.

The 1987 Rob Reiner-directed movie fits the teasing description Guettel gave for his next project, while speaking backstage at the 2005 Tony Awards. While hesitant to specifically name his next musical due to "legal reasons," he did say it would have a "fairy tale" nature and would involve "a lot of swordfighting."

"The Princess Bride" delighted audiences with its mix of sincere medieval magic and mocking parody of the swashbuckling film genre. The flick starred Cary Elwes and Robin Wright as each other's true love, and Chris Sarandon as the evil prince who would keep them apart. The film also starred Mandy Patinkin as a swordsman out for vengeance, Christopher Guest as another baddie, Wallace Shawn and Andre the Giant as two unlikely compatriots, and Billy Crystal and Carol Kane as an ancient wizard and his wife.

The material would make for a decided shift to the lighthearted for Guettel, whose two previous musicals, Floyd Collins and The Light in the Piazza, both examine the darker and moodier sides of human nature.

Goldman is a famed screenwriter known for the films "Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid," "All the President's Men" and "Marathon Man." He also wrote the classic examination of the Broadway world, "The Season."

OMG!!!! This could be so totally awesome!!

Only like 2 and a bit days left and the 2 and a bit days are rather full. Not sure when I'll be able to finish packing and spend time with my family. I am so scared about moving. I just wish my family weren't going to be so far away. I'd be looking forward to this so much more if I knew that I could see them again before Christmas. I guess Christmas isn't that far away though. Only about four months, of course there is a chance I might not get home for Christmas but I really want to!!

Anyway I'm off to see a movie with Rosie tonight, Danielle cancelled. There's drama going on between her and Rosie right now. They both apparently hate each other which is interesting. Oh well, gonna see wedding crashers which looks so good! Then tomorrow I'm off to the bank in the morning with my mom before meeting up with Rosie again to go to codonas and see Herbie: Fully Loaded. Then that night I'm meeting up with Julie for either a meal or drinks. Leaving me with only Friday to see Charc, Danielle, Jenny and (especially) Christine and Val since I haven't seen the 2 of them since like June. So crazy! Won't be seeing Merel again for a while as I don't think she's coming back from Holland in time which sucks but oh well. Not much I can do.

Only eight days left of living in Scotland and I'm no where near ready to move. My room is an absolute mess although this time it's not really my fault. It's messy because me and my mom have been going through drawers and my closet and stuff and trying to sort out what I'm taking, what's staying and what's getting thrown out. Makes for a mess.

Anyway, should be going out tonight with a couple friends, will be fun :) May be my last night out in town before moving. So crazy! Going out tomorrow night too but for dinner at Little Italy. Not much else is happening, spending more time on organising all my stuff today. Oh, found out yesterday I have a single room in an all girls dorm and am on the ground floor. Not really sure if this is good or bad, but I do know I wish I wasn't on the ground floor. I'm not sure why but I just wish I was at least one floor up. Oh well, nothing I can do about it.

I'm now definately moving to Canada to go to UBC, need BBC to get in and got AAB so I am in. Also should get first year credit for 2 or 3 classes...hopefully.

Been to Italy and Australia. So much fun! Can't believe that in less than 2 weeks I will be moving. It will go by so fast. I just want to spend time with friends but I have so much that needs to be done.
My stomach is killing me. So much pain.

It's apparently offical: I am done with highschool. I have left. I did not graduate, I left. Stupid ceremony. But at least the speech the head boy and girl gave was funny. The guest speaker person was so boring, I have no idea what she was going on about. I was more worried that the guy sitting next to me was going to puke. He was way hungover. Last couple days were so fun! Almost everyone in the year went down to Allan park Wednesday afternoon and most stayed until the police showed up and took away all the (remaining) alcohol. Really need to post some of my pics up on a photobucket thing. Had English exam on Friday. Did not go well. At all. Very bad. But only worth 30% and that's all that will be said of that. Math exam is this coming Friday. Have really not done enough revision. I'm going to try a past paper tomorrow and hopefully will do better than the last one I tried which I would have failed. Great fun. This time in two months I will be in Australia!! So very cool!

This was my last Thursday ever in highschool. I only have 4 days left of school, plus an hour or 2 on Thursday morning which is the leavers ceremony and then my 3 exams. After that no more Cults Academy. It's pretty sad. And so surreal, I can't believe that I'm basically done. Can't believe that I'll be moving in like 3 and a half months. It's all so crazy!

I finally passed my driving test on Tuesday after moving my test back twice (only 5 minors, pretty good) but of course now that I've spent so much time learning I have nothing to drive. I don't have my own car and it seems basically impossible right now to get me insured on either of my parents cars especially only for 2 months until I go on holiday for a month then move like 2 weeks after getting home. So crap. I'm so pissed off and I have to go to work which I do not like and find extremely boring. It's crap. I can't wait until the end of June.
